:: ValidationIntro
(set: $steps to $steps + 1)

<script>
if (window.tecaaXapi) {
  window.tecaaXapi.markSessionStart();
  window.tecaaXapi.send(
    window.tecaaXapi.base(
      'http://adlnet.gov/expapi/verbs/initialized',
      'initialized'
    )
  );
  window.tecaaXapi.send(
    window.tecaaXapi.base(
      'http://adlnet.gov/expapi/verbs/launched',
      'launched'
    )
  );
}
</script>

Validation keeps statements technically correct and interoperable.
For this project, always confirm required fields and use stable absolute IRIs.

[[Continue->ValidationChecks]]

:: ValidationChecks
(set: $steps to $steps + 1)

<script>
if (window.tecaaXapi) {
  window.tecaaXapi.send(
    window.tecaaXapi.base(
      'http://adlnet.gov/expapi/verbs/experienced',
      'experienced'
    )
  );
}
</script>

Checklist before sending a statement:
1. Required fields exist: `actor`, `verb`, `object`, `version`
2. Actor identifier has valid structure
3. Verb/object IDs are proper absolute IRIs
4. Timestamp is present and valid ISO-8601

[[Open quiz->QuizIRI]]

